                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12913999" author="srowen" created="Thu, 23 Sep 2010 13:21:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Robin is this safely puntable to 0.5?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12914882" author="robinanil" created="Sat, 25 Sep 2010 22:44:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for implementing logNormalization in Vector. has tests and adds logNormalization in DictionaryVectorizer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also changed the behaviour of DictionaryVectorizer.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If tf vectors are being generated, the final merge stage normalizes it.&lt;br/&gt;
If tfidf vectors are being generated, no normalization is done in tf stage, normalization is done in merge after idf is calculated&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also fixed a bug which caused normalization not to happen if chunk size was one( we were renaming the partial directory as a speed hack)&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12914976" author="robinanil" created="Sun, 26 Sep 2010 14:39:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Completed rewrite of Bayes and CBayes trainer using vectors. Very compact, but not in the same pattern as earlier package. So not using O(size of document) memory like the earlier version.  Uses O(Feature size) memory. Easier to maintain and store/read vectors, but bounded by feature size. Randomized input vectors will prove to be very useful here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comments welcome. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will now write the in-memory Classifier, and make a 20newsgroups example &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12914994" author="tdunning" created="Sun, 26 Sep 2010 17:32:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Feature vectors should be sparse nearly always.  That should make the memory O(document size) again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917228" author="robinanil" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 18:54:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Model, trainer and classifier completed with basic tests. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Now onto documentation, main and twenty newsgroups example&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917231" author="srowen" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 19:09:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a pretty large change &amp;#8211; how good do you feel about sticking it in just before we &apos;freeze&apos; for polish and fixes for a week? While I think in general smaller changes are safer now, it&apos;s up to your judgment on that point.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917232" author="robinanil" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 19:13:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I would like one review cycle on it before I check it in. I can always work on smaller changes over the week as we tweak the whole release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917240" author="robinanil" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 20:48:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I am committing the log normalizer patch first. That is pretty much independent of the classifier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917248" author="hudson" created="Sat, 2 Oct 2010 22:59:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #364 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/364/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/364/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-287&quot; title=&quot;Bayes Classifier should use Vector as input&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-287&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-287&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Adding lognormalize option to dictionary vectorizer&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918075" author="robinanil" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 18:03:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Set of classes to train and classify vectors using naivebayes &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918696" author="robinanil" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 22:37:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committing this patch now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918722" author="hudson" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 23:59:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #377 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/377/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/377/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
